my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) All crew engaged in connecting the lifting wires to wear a safety harness connected to the fall arrest equipment; 
c) All crew involved with the hatch opening or closing procedure must be trained and have a full understanding with regard to the procedure; 
d) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if necessary; 
e) Ensure that no person(s) are on the hatch covers during operation; 
f) Any crew / personnel not directly involved in hatch cover operations should stay well clear.

a) All crew involved with the hatch cover operations must be fully trained with regard to the procedure;
b) The Master or Chief Officer must be and remain in overall charge of the operation; 
c) Consult the Company Manual 'Procedures for the Safe Operation of Hatches, Cranes, Bulkheads and Tweendecks'. 
d) Only fully trained crew are permitted to operate the cargo crane; 
e) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
f) Ensure that no person(s) are in the hold during the operation; 
g) Ensure that the safety pins are in position.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Emergency stops tested and ready; 
d) Crew vigilance - Constant monitoring of the task; 
e) Ensure that the person operating the cargo has a clear view of the hatch covers at all times; 
g) Any crew / personnel not directly involved in hatch cover operations should stay well clear; 
h) Cargo crane signalling equipment i.e. whistle, PA must be operational; 
i) Consult Company Manual 'Procedures for the Safe Operation of Hatches and Bulkheads' / 'Procedures for the Safe Operation of Hatches, Cranes, Bulkheads and Tweendecks'.

a) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
b) Ensure the cleats have been disengaged; 
c) Ensure all lifting wires and shackles are visually inspected and condition checked prior to every use; 
d) Any wires or shackles found in poor condition or damaged must be removed immediately and replaced; 
e) All lifting appliances should be stowed accordingly, protected from the elements.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, safety harness, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided. Use portable lighting if necessary; 
c) Crew vigilance - Particular attention should be paid to walking on deck i.e. precipitation; 
d) In the event of high winds, consideration must be made to postpone operations until the weather improves.

a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, high-visibility vest, etc.; 
b) Adequate lighting to be provided; 
c) Communication must be established, via VHF or crane signals, between the crane operator and crew working below; 
d) All crew / personnel not directly involved in crane operations should stay well clear.
